column5: Hi all, Was out yesterday afternoon putting around on Wabigoon, I was casting for bass in a back bay when I noticed the water temp was in the 70f range, main lake basin was in high 60's. Granted these are surface temps, but pretty high for this time of year in my limited 15 years experience of NWO lake fishing.
Looks like July-August main lake surface temps. Too soon though..... Pooch
That's not going to sting at all,when I dive in,bath water!
